      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a profound and lonely truth that you are describing, and it is okay to admit that the spark has gone out for now. Many people in your situation feel this exact hollowness, but the shell itself is the only vessel that can ever hold a new life, even if that life starts with just silence and rest. You do not need to explain the disappearance of your inner self to the world; you can simply choose to stop performing the role until you find a reason to feel again.",
      "source": "target",
